=== Adjective ===
'''gay''' (''comparative:'' '''gayer''', ''superlative:'' '''gayest''')

#[[happy]], [[joyful]], and [[lively]]
#[[festive]], [[bright]], [[colourful]]
#:''Don we now our '''gay''' apparel''
#:''Pennsylvania Dutch include the plain folk and the '''gay''' folk.''
#[[homosexual]]
#[[typical]] of [[homosexual]] [[appearance]] or [[behaviour]]
#(''slang'') [[boring]], [[unappealing]], bad or of low [[quality]]

==== Usage notes ====
*''Gay'' is almost exclusively used today in its ''homosexual'' and related senses, and, latterly, in the sense of ''boring, etc''.  The earlier uses of ''festive'', ''colorful'', ''bright'' can still be found but have fallen out of fashion and are liable to misunderstanding.
*''Gay'' is preferred to ''homosexual'' by many gay people as their own term for themselves, claiming that ''homosexual'' is a medical term and hence too clinical.
*Some object to sense 5 because they feel it encourages a negative perception of homosexuality.

